Body: Description: All websites are blocked except Facebook and Instagram, which are mentioned in the deny list.
What We've Learned Updated: Client is unable to block Facebook and Instagram.
Next Steps Updated: Will have to provide instructions on how to create the proper CAP policy.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Marian Ilies, Andre Le Roux, mohammad.azam Azam

What We've Learned Updated: Client got back to us stating the issue came up and the network extension disappeared.
Next Steps Updated: Asked for availability for a remote session.
Invitation updated. Attendees: Marian Ilies, mohammad.azam Azam

What We've Learned Updated: Got back into a remote session with the client and on a new MAC OS, he can't block sites on it.
Checked the intercept traffic VPN and it was enabled.
Checked the network extension and it was missing indeed.
Asked to restart and check again but that did not work.
He did not had anymore time to take a look and we agreed to call back tomorrow at 12:30  PM IST.
Next Steps Updated: Next we will connect remote to take a look and try to re-install the EPP and also allow the EPP to have full access over the device.

What We've Learned Updated: Got back on another remote session today with the client to troubleshoot.
Connected remote and went to allow the eppclient to have access to the full disk and accessibility.
Tried to check again for network extension but it was missing completely.
Also we tried to allow the eppnotifier but could not find it at all being present under security and privacy nor under notifications.
Tried to uninstall the app but client messed it by typing in the wrong password multiple times and asked to reschedule for later today while he takes care of this password issue.
Asked him to just uninstall the app so we can try a fresh installation.
Next Steps Updated: Will have to set up another remote session.

What We've Learned Updated: Connected remote for the 3rd time and we managed to re-install the EPP but this time we allowed the eppclient to have full access to the disk, accessibility and bluetooth.
Also we disabled/enabled back the intercept VPN from the computer settings, and updated the policy on the MAC and now the network extension was enabled accordingly.
We tried multiple portals and all of them were properly blocked.
